cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving agent generalization in physics-based simulated and real-robot tasks.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel algorithm for improving domain randomization, which is a popular technique in AI for improving domain transfer.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the effects of domain randomization on policy learning and proposes a new algorithm for learning a parameter sampling strategy.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve visual perception in the simulated or real-robot tasks.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with improving agent generalization in control tasks.
